text: Jabłoń is a village in Parczew County, Lublin Voivodeship, in eastern Poland. It is the seat of the gmina (administrative district) called Gmina Jabłoń. It lies approximately north-east of Parczew and north-east of the regional capital Lublin. The village has a population of 1,251. ==References== Category:Villages in Parczew County Category:Siedlce Governorate Category:Kholm Governorate Category:Lublin Voivodeship (1919–1939)
